    "body": "## Problem\r\nVirtual lines above a line always have the `foldcolumn` of the line below. (#39892)\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nCheck if the line below the virtual one is inside a fold that starts higher up or if it's the start of a fold. In the latter case, don't show anything in `foldcolumn` for the virtual line.\r\n\r\nFirst test is for the reproducible example above. Second test is for preserving current behavior when a virtual line is inside a fold (`foldcolumn` continues through the virtual line).\r\n\r\nCloses #39892 ",
    "closed_at": "2026-05-20T11:56:40Z",
